{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17500892","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17500892"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:19:36+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:19:36+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1693"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1693","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1693"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.03,0.75,0.12,0.06,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1693"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115067"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1693","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1693"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1693"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97075"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"898"},{"type":"tags","id":"2706"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"8118"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"6386"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7061"},{"type":"contributions","id":"33920"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40663"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42368"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43093"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115067","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/115067"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 63-year-old man presents to the emergency department with sudden onset of shortness of breath. He is breathless at rest and only able to speak in short sentences. On examination, the patient is in obvious distress and sitting upright in the bed. His pulse rate is 110/min, blood pressure 130/85 mmHg, respiratory rate 28/min, oxygen saturation on room air is 90%, and temperature 37.2\u00b0C. There are coarse crepitations in the lower lung zones bilaterally on auscultation, dullness to percussion and decreased vocal resonance. His chest X-ray is shown (image).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHigh-flow oxygen is given by a non-rebreather mask.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Nebulised adrenaline","Furosemide IV","Nebulised salbutamol","Sublingual glyceryl trinitrate","Morphine IV"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe patient above is suffering from acute pulmonary oedema (APO). This condition often presents with rapid onset severe dyspnoea and orthopnoea in addition to tachypnoea and tachycardia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInitial treatment involves positioning the patient upright and administering high flow oxygen if saturations are less than 94%. \u003Cstrong\u003EFurosemide\u003C/strong\u003E is the mainstay of treatment, with \u003Cstrong\u003Eglyceryl trinitrate\u003C/strong\u003E indicated if the patient\u0027s clinical response to oxygen and furosemide is insufficient.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMorphine\u003C/strong\u003E can be considered if the patient is acutely anxious and distressed but can also help in tolerating continuous positive airway pressure (CPAP) ventilation if required for escalating symptoms. CPAP should be started promptly if symptoms do not improve with the above interventions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENebulised adrenaline\u003C/strong\u003E is indicated for situations involving inflammation of the upper airways such as acute laryngotracheobronchitis (croup). In this patient above suffering from APO, nebulised adrenaline is unlikely to provide any benefit.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENebulised salbutamol\u003C/strong\u003E is indicated for situations of bronchospasm unresponsive to conventional therapy such as acute severe asthma or exacerbations of COPD.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Furosemide PO or IV is the initial intervention for acute pulmonary oedema."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Acute cardiogenic pulmonary oedema. In: Therapeutic guidelines [Internet]. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited; [updated 2023; cited 2025 Jul 15]. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97075"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1693"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"17352"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"17352","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/17352"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/4613a692-0b14-4e0f-af4d-45773f5aae30.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/4613a692-0b14-4e0f-af4d-45773f5aae30.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":293,"height":308}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97075","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/97075"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-22T09:05:55+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-22T09:05:55+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1693"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115067"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":